article.headline: Ark.-Little Rock 66, Florida Atlantic 59
article.story: BOCA RATON, Fla. -- Shane Edwards scored 17 points to lead Arkansas-Little Rock past Florida Atlantic 66-59 on Thursday night, extending the Owls' losing streak to 13 games and keeping them winless in the Sun Belt Conference. The Trojans (15-6, 8-2) led 35-24 at halftime and by as many as 15 in the second half. The Owls (4-18, 0-10) cut the lead to five at 58-53 with 6:13 left on a 3-pointer by Paul Graham III, but that was their last field goal of the game. Graham hit 6 of 7 free throws for Florida Atlantic's remaining scoring. Arkansas-Little Rock was 26 of 48 from the field (54.2 percent) compared to Florida Atlantic's 19 of 60 (31.7 percent). Steven Moore added 12 points for the Trojans. Mike Smith, who sat out six games for violating team rules, played 14 minutes with two points and four rebounds. Graham led the Owls with 22 points and five assists.
